5\. Screenings Record

  


Requirements

The Screenings record is used to track specific screenings and the outcomes. It is tied to the Child record and is accessible from the Child record.

  


Screenings

  * Section: Screening (show child name and screening date)
    * Child (automatically linked back to child record)
    * Child's Birth Date (automatic from child)
    * Django ID; used for imports
    * Screening Date
    * Screened By (text)
  * Section: Results
    * See below
  * Section: Referrals
    * See below
  * Section: Notes
    * Notes (memo)



  


Here is the screenshot of the results. ![](data:image/png;base64,)

Both spreadsheets would be automatically populated with all screening types. The rows would be gray until data is entered. The Results spreadsheet should NOT allow duplicate rows. The Referrals can.

  


The Referrals RG should be sorted by the list order of each of the columns (Screening, Referral Type, and Referral). The Screening column should be required.

  


The Screening type should be a list of: (in this order throughout the system)

  * Development
  * ECHO Vision
  * LIONS Vision
  * OAE Hearing
  * Tympanometry
  * Pure Tone Hearing
  * Social Emotional
  * Articulation



  


New screening type records will show the following rows in the Screening column of the Results and Referrals RGs 

  * Development
  * ECHO Vision
  * OAE Hearing
  * Social Emotional
  * Articulation



  


The Screening Result should be a list of:

  * Pass
  * Refer (renamed from Fail)
  * Not Done
  * Rescreen (renamed from Questionable)
  * Untestable



  


The Social Emotional Score/Cutoff should only be editable for the Social Emotional Row.

  


The referral type should be a list of:

  * Screening
  * Program



(Note the order.)

  


If the Referral Type is a Screening, the Referral options should be:

  * Behavior Team
  * Developmental Evaluation
  * C2K Specialist (renamed from ECMH Specialist)
  * LIONS Vision
  * Medical
  * Other
  * Rescreen Development
  * Rescreen Hearing
  * Rescreen Vision
  * Special Hearing
  * Articulation Evaluation (only visible for Development, Articulation, and Social Emotional)
  * Articulation Rescreen (only visible for Development, Articulation, and Social Emotional)



  


If the Referral Type is a Program, the Referral options should be:

  * Preschool Special Ed
  * CPP
  * C2K
  * Home Visiting
  * EHS
  * Head Start
  * Other



  


The Other Referral should be read-only unless Other is specified. In that case, it should be required.

  


If the Referral Type is a Screening, the Outcome options should be:

  * Qualified for Special Ed (or Q if abbreviated)
  * Did Not Qualify (DNQ if abbreviated)
  * Pass
  * Fail
  * Refused
  * No Show
  * Could Not Contact



  


If the Referral Type is a Program, the Outcome options should be:

  * Enrolled
  * Refused
  * No Show
  * Could Not Contact



  


When migrating, we will blank out Pending outcomes.

  


Development Specification

Matthias Miller 07/28/2020: You can think of Screenings as a "doctor visit" and each of these screening types as a "test/diagnosis" that they perform. For example, one "doctor visit" you may test 3 things. Another "doctor visit", you may test 1.

  


Matthias Miller 07/16/2020: For the sake of indexing and reporting, I think we need to autofill an RG with all screening types and results. I don't believe we need to search on any of the outcomes. (This will let us use an index at some point of we need to for speed purposes. Or maybe we can just use a macro.)
